# CODEOWNERS — auto-request review on files whose silent modification

# could destroy review intent, break publishing, weaken security, or

# invalidate CI gates. No wildcard: routine PRs are not auto-assigned.

# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customizations/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# --- Review & quality gates (silently disabling these defeats the whole review process) ---

/.coderabbit.yaml @Vijay431 # CodeRabbit rules — bad change disables AI review gate
/.github/CODEOWNERS @Vijay431 # circular — anyone editing this can unprotect everything else
/.github/workflows/ci.yml @Vijay431 # main PR gate (lint, unit, integration, audit) — can be neutered
/.github/workflows/pr-commit-size.yml @Vijay431 # 10-file / 400-line cap enforcement
/.husky/ @Vijay431 # local pre-commit / commit-msg hooks
/scripts/check-commit-size.sh @Vijay431 # commit-size script CI calls
/scripts/commit-size-excludes.txt @Vijay431 # bypass list for commit-size check — abuse vector

# --- Release / publishing (bad change publishes broken build or leaks tokens) ---

/.github/workflows/release.yml @Vijay431 # publishes to VS Code Marketplace + Open VSX with VSCE_PAT/OVSX_PAT
/package.json @Vijay431 # extension manifest: publisher, version, engines, contributes
/.vscodeignore @Vijay431 # controls what ships in .vsix — can leak source/secrets

# --- Supply chain (bad change = arbitrary code on dev/CI machines) ---

/pnpm-lock.yaml @Vijay431 # dependency integrity
/pnpm-workspace.yaml @Vijay431 # owns pnpm overrides + allowBuilds (install-time scripts)
/.npmrc @Vijay431 # registry + auth behavior
/.github/dependabot.yml @Vijay431 # auto-PR config — bad change stops security updates silently

# --- Build correctness (broken bundle = broken extension on every user's machine) ---

/esbuild.config.ts @Vijay431 # bundle externals (lazy services) + 100KB core budget
/tsconfig.json @Vijay431 # strict mode + target — relaxing silently weakens type safety

